name: Haunted Highway
overview:
Haunted Highway, is a paranormal investigation, reality television series, produced by BASE Productions, that began airing on the Syfy network July 3, 2012.

The series features two teams of investigators; Jack Osbourne, investigator Dana Workman, and Fact or Faked: Paranormal Files investigators Jael de Pardo and Devin Marble.

On the 5th episode of the series, Osbourne announced that he was diagnosed with multiple sclerosis and temporarily stepped down as host of the series.

On April 22, 2013 it was announced that the series had been renewed for a 6-episode 2nd Season set to premiere in the fall of 2013.

episodes.name: Bear Lake Beast; Vergas Hairy Man
episodes.overview: Strange creatures are sought in Utah and Minnesota in the debut of a series featuring paranormal investigations at locales along remote roads.

episodes.name: Darkman of Standing Rock; Blackstar Shadow Man
episodes.overview: Investigators explore the North Dakota prairie on horseback as they search for a creature who hunts weak souls.

episodes.name: Utah Skinwalker; Ozark Howler
episodes.overview: Jack and Dana track a shape-shifting demon while Devin and Jael search for a howling Ozark creature.

episodes.name: El Dorado Hell Hounds; Georgia Skinstealer
episodes.overview: Spectral dogs are sought in Nevada, and the search for a demon unfolds in Georgia.

episodes.name: Louisiana Swamp Woman; Pioneer Cemetery
episodes.overview: A Louisiana swamp and a pioneer cemetery are visited.

episodes.name: Silver City Ghost Town; Shunka Warakin
episodes.overview: An Old West ghost town in Idaho is visited for a paranormal probe, and a prairie monster is sought in Montana in the Season 1 finale.

episodes.name: Island of the Lost Souls
episodes.overview: Jack Osbourne, Dana Workman, Jael de Pardo, and Devin Marble team up for the first time to investigate the Island of Dry Tortugas. The whole team is needed to explore the massive amount of paranormal activity surrounding this remote island!

episodes.name: Manchac Swamp/Moonville Tunnel
episodes.overview: Jack Osbourne and Dana Workman travel to Louisiana to a swamp town where hundreds of people died during a funeral for one woman. Meanwhile, Jael de Pardo and Devin Marble travel to southeast Ohio to investigate a haunted tunnel.

episodes.name: Beast of Bray Road/Tonopah Mine
episodes.overview: Devin Marble and Jael de Pardo hunt down the Beast of Bray Road in the snowy woods of Wisconsin, while Jack Osbourne and Dana Workman take to a haunted mine in Nevada with frightening results.

episodes.name: Lake Murray Beast/The Donner Party
episodes.overview: Jael and Devin go fishing for the Lake Murray Monster in South Carolina while Dana and Jack search for the Donner party in Truckee, California.

episodes.name: Shades of Death/Bridge of Doom
episodes.overview: Jael de Pardo and Devin Marble investigate a tragic railroad disaster in Ashtabula, Ohio, while Jack Osbourne and Dana Workman explore a reportedly haunted area in New Jersey known as Shades of Death Road.
